    <h2>What does "open source" mean?</h2>

    <p>Everything that makes this project work has been published. All the artwork, script files, source code and other ingredients are available for you to download.</p>

    <p>All this stuff has been released under a <a href="/{{lang}}/legal.html">license</a> that lets you change them and use them in new ways (provided you stick to a few simple rules).</p>

    <p>You can contribute back to this project, and your work can be of benefit to others, but you don't have to.</p>

    <p>This project can continue if I die, or if I lose interest and take it away, as long as a copy survives somewhere.</p>

    <nav class="nav--bar">
        {{#> Button href="https://github.com/dyslexic-charactersheets" type="light" cls="btn--bgicon button-github"}}{{__ "GitHub"}}{{/Button}}
